selected papers themselves, this volume opens with a foreword by David Fisher, Alexander Lubotzky, and Gregory Margulis, as well as a substantial introductory essay by Zimmer recounting the course of his career in mathematics. The volume closes with an afterword by Fisher on the most recent developments around the Zimmer program.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 24. Aug 2021) 0aErgodic theory. 0aGroup actions (Mathematics) 0aGroup actions (Mathematics). 0aGroup actions. 0aLie groups. 7aMATHEMATICS / General.2bisacsh1 aFisher, David, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aFisher, David, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aFisher, David.1 aKatok, A., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aLabourie, F., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aLabourie, Franqois, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aLashof, Richard K., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aLewis, J., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aLubotzky, Alexander, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aLubotzky, Alexander.1 aMargulis, Gregory, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMargulis, Gregory.1 aMozes, S., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aNevo, Amos, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aSpatzier, Ralf J., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aStuck, Garrett, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aZimmer, Robert J., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of Chicago Press Complete eBook-Package